<item>
            <title>[HBASE-725] Maximum ColumnKey Lookup</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-725</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When working with time series data, relative columnKeys &apos;indexes&apos; are routinely shared between the columnFamilies of a given row. To acquire the maximum key and increment it for the next columnKey, you must first get all the keys. A quick lookup of the last columnKey would benefit as the column size grows over time. &lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12399732">HBASE-725</key>
            <summary>Maximum ColumnKey Lookup</summary>
                <type id="2" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/issuetypes/newfeature.png">New Feature</type>
